&nbsp;
The banknotes were spread throughout Europe, particularly in France. The banknotes were made of 20, 50 and 100 euros and were sold at 10% of the value. The quality of the banknotes was excellent, to the point that the Bce coined the term "Napoli Group" in order to qualify the groups of Naples and the partner hinterland capable of producing a high quality counterfeiting. It is disputed in this case the aggravating of the mafia method because the activity of production and sale of counterfeit notes served to finance the Camorristic clan Mazzarella.
&nbsp;
During the investigation, 3 French citizens who had just purchased the banknotes were arrested and were going to Capodichino airport to return to their country. Within a year of investigation the introit made by the group of falsiers has been quantified in 6 million euros for a nominal value of the banknotes produced of approximately 60 million euros false. The counterfeit currency is still in circulation in all European countries, where daily it is found and seized.&nbsp;
