AGI -&nbsp;&nbsp; There are thirteen citizens of San Donato Milanese and Chiaravalle who, supported by the No Stadium Committee in San Donato Milanese and assisted by a pool of lawyers, on 22 March they filed official complaint at the headquarters of Milan of the Regional Administrative Court to request the annulment of the acts adopted by the Squeri administration in favor of the San Francesco Sanese stadium in Milan.
&nbsp;
The application - a document of twenty-three and twenty-three pages - specifically asks for the annulment of the following acts: the deliberation of the Municipal Council of San Donato Milanese n. 15, published on 25 January 2024, subject to the "initial proposal of urban variant" with attached evaluation favorable to the viability for the construction of the stadium; the Active Plan (Integrated Programme of Intervention) approved by the Municipal Administration, aiming to allow the realization of the system that in the intentions of the club should be 70 thousand places.
&nbsp;
"In the face of the refusal of the mayor Squeri and the political forces that support him in the municipal council to seriously dialogue with the citizens, we have held faith to the commitment that we had taken from the first moment of the constitution of the committee, that is to make any effort and to pursue all the lawful roads possible to stop a project that we believe harmful to our territory" says Innocente Curci, one of the referents of the Committee No Stadio to San Donato Milanese,
&nbsp;
"All the applicants, as well as many other citizens of San Donato Milanese, Milan and San Giuliano Milanese, would be damaged by the realization of the work and we felt the duty to expose our reasons to the administrative judges, convinced that they can be heard".
<br> "We have studied the papers that we have been able to hold on to the AC Milan Project; in our opinion we are faced with numerous illegitimate profiles that spoil the acts in question. In particular, the municipal council's deliberation has many technical and legal issues, highlighted in the appeal - declares the lawyer Ilaria Battistini, a professional commissioned by the applicants who is providing support to the committee also regarding the request for a citizen referendum deposited in the municipality -. We hope that, as a result of the notification of the appeal, the Commune is convinced of the unrealization of the work.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
We are also confident that the other public administrations we have made aware of the act of appeal (Milan Metropolitan City and Lombardy Region) take into account the evidenced and widely documented by the applicants, even before the judges express themselves in the merits". Only in an exemplary way, specify the applicants, one of the elements emerged from the study of the cards and reported in the resort is that on 28 September 2023 the company SportLifeCity - society that Milan has unlike declared to have acquired last June 8 as owner of the area San Francesco - "unless being not owner neither having the availability of the areas, it still presented in an official way to the Municipality of San Donato Milanese a proposal. It is from that specific act - the applicants continue - that started the municipal administrative process, with the consequent production of technical documents from the offices and the approval of the deliberation of Giunta". Another procedural relief that is advanced in the application is attributable to the approval procedure of the municipal decision n. 15 of 24/01/2024, the one that contains the proposal of urban variant.
&nbsp;
The Junta would in fact "overturn the regulatory process, putting black on white in the first line a "positive assessment regarding the viability of the Initial Proposal", including the Technical Document of Preliminary Analysis. By doing so, the Junta has subverted the prerogatives of the City Council, arbitrarily relegated to ratifying (in fact, to things already agreed between the parties involved) the eventual Program Agreement. This determines a clear illegitimate nature of the deliberation itself of Giunta which, by exceeding the regional norm, decides to postpone to a moment after the intervention of the City Council".
&nbsp;
"In these months - says Annalisa Molgora, another representative of the Committee that yesterday organized a protest flashmob to Chiaravalle, area within the border of Milan where the Cistercian Abbey arises affected by the impact of a possible plant - we promoted a petition addressed to the mayor of San Donato signed by more than three thousand citizens who asks to say no to the new stadium in San Donato; we have been active with numerous initiatives to inform and discuss the merits of the proposal of urban variant that Milan would definitely approve; we have relationships and are collaborating on the territory with numerous other associative realities that are manifesting concern and need to be involved. Now we have started the legal battle and will launch a fundraising campaign that allows us to cope with the many expenses we will face. We are strongly determined and ask citizens to support us again," he concluded.&nbsp;

